  "name": "Morrison COU2 — Non-cannulated F1717 compression-bending MRL-5 fully-assessed credibility package",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct at Model Risk Level 5. This package covers COU2 (the clinical-use extrapolation context) under the Morrison archetype, building on the Nagaraja COU1 validation foundation. All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors are assessed at high rigor commensurate with MRL 5. Full uncertainty quantification (UQ) and global sensitivity analysis (GSA) are linked as subordinate evidence artefacts. The model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two independent laboratories; all QoI differences fall within the pre-established ±10 % acceptance bound and the normalised validation metric E/u_val < 1.96 for all three QoIs. Decision: Accepted.",
